definition.value: Parrots, also known as psittacines /ˈsɪtəsaɪnz/, are birds of the roughly 393 species in 92 genera that make up the order Psittaciformes, found in most tropical and subtropical regions.
A parakeet is any one of a large number of small to medium-sized species of parrot, in multiple genera, that generally have long tail feathers.
Kielbasa (from Polish kiełbasa)[a] is any type of meat sausage from Poland, and a staple of Polish cuisine.
Pork sausage is sausage made with pork meat.
A whole animal liver that is obtained from a turkey.
Liver from a turkey.
A fillet cut of a snapper fish
A process of applying a seasoning mixture to a given food.
Food which has had seasoning applied to it.
Roast beef is a dish of beef which is roasted. Essentially prepared as a main meal, the leftovers are often used in sandwiches and sometimes are used to make hash.
Bird's eye chili is a chili pepper, a variety from the species Capsicum annuum, commonly found in Ethiopia and across Southeast Asia.

A hamburger (short: burger) is a sandwich consisting of one or more cooked patties of ground meat, usually beef, placed inside a sliced bread roll or bun. The patty may be pan fried, grilled, or flame broiled.

Meat and bone meal (MBM) is a product of the rendering industry. It is typically about 48–52% protein, 33–35% ash, 8–12% fat, and 4–7% water. It is primarily used in the formulation of animal feed to improve the amino acid profile of the feed.
Packaged food is food that has been placed in a container of some kind.
A process that applies packaging material to a food product for preservation, shipping and/or presentation purposes.

Poultry by-product meal (PBM) is a high-protein commodity used as a major component in some pet foods. It is made from grinding clean, rendered parts of poultry carcasses and can contain bones, offal and undeveloped eggs, but only contains feathers that are unavoidable in the processing of the poultry parts.
A fillet cut of a tuna fish.
A roll is a small, often round loaf of bread served as a meal accompaniment (eaten plain or with butter).  A bun is a small, sometimes sweet, bread, or bread roll.
Roasted food is more structured food that is generally subjected to a dry heat cooking process at higher oven temperature than baking.
The liquid contents of one or more eggs.

A guajillo chili or guajillo chile is a variety of chile pepper of the species *Capsicum annuum* which is widely used in the cuisine of Mexico. Its heat (rating 2,500 to 5,000 on the Scoville scale) is considered mild to medium.
Tinfoil barb is a member of the Barbonymus genus, a ray-finned fish in the family Cyprinidae.
The brown bean is chestnut brown colored bean with a small white-eye which originates in Scandanavia.

The borlotti bean is a variety of common bean (Phaseolus vulgaris) first bred in Colombia as the cargamanto. It is also known as the cranberry bean, Roman bean, romano bean saluggia bean, gadhra bean or rosecoco bean.
A whole dried bean is a bean resulting from natural or mechanical air drying applied to a bean or bean pod.
A seed of a bean plant from one of several genera of the flowering plant family (Fabaceae).
Comminuted food is the output of a comminution process that reduces solid materials from one average particle size to a smaller average particle size, by crushing, grinding, cutting, vibrating, etc.
A rehydrated bean is a dried bean subjected to a rehydration process
A split pigeon pea is a dried pigeon pea split into halves.
A kidney shaped seed of a kidney bean plant, a varietal of a common bean plant (Phaseolus vulgaris).

Cooked bean material is the bean material output of a cooking process applied to dry, rehydrated, or raw (fresh) beans.
A leguminous fruit pod from a plant in the dry bean class.
A shell bean pod is a leguminous fruit pod from a shell bean plant.
A bean pod is a fruit pod from a bean plant
A green bean food product that derives from raw whole green bean pods.
A food product made from the pink bean plant.
A food product made from a scandinavian brown bean plant.
An edible pod of a hyacinth bean plant which contains immature seeds
A seed of a bambara groundnut plant (Vigna subterranea).
